yond the official world of Stalinism. Resistance ranged across a spectrum from violent strikes to the passive resistance that was a virtual way of life for millions and took many forms, from foot dragging and negligence to feigned ignorance and false compliance. Contending with Stalinism also highlights the problematic nature of resistance as an analytical category and stresses the ambiguous nature of the phenomenon. The topics addressed include working-class strikes, peasant rebellions, black-market crimes, official corruption, and homosexual and ethnic subcultures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGovernment, Resistance tozSoviet Union. 4aHistory. 4aSoviet & East European History. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh1 aHarris, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHealey, Dan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcdonald, Tracy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorthrop, Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOsokina, Elena A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRossman, Jeffrey J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aViola, Lynne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aViola, Lynne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171729140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501717291423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501717291.jpg  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS 